#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Find Peak Element (Binary Search)

Peak element wo hota hai jo apne dono neighbors se greater ho.
Question mein bola hai nums[-1] = nums[n] = -infinity,
matlab boundary elements bhi peak ho sakte hain.

Hume O(log n) time chahiye -> Binary Search use karenge.

Key Idea:
Agar hum kisi mid index par khade hain, to 3 cases ho sakte hain:

Case 1:
nums[mid] > nums[mid-1] AND nums[mid] > nums[mid+1]
-> mid hi peak hai -> return mid

Case 2:
nums[mid] > nums[mid-1]
-> Matlab array increasing slope par hai
-> Peak right side mein milega
-> low = mid + 1

Case 3:
nums[mid] < nums[mid-1]
-> Matlab array decreasing slope par hai
-> Peak left side mein milega
-> high = mid - 1

Important Observation:
Hum hamesha slope ki direction mein move karte hain,
kyunki peak hamesha increasing slope ke end par milta hai.

Steps:
1. Edge cases check karo:
   - Agar n == 1 -> return 0
   - Agar first element > second -> return 0
   - Agar last element > second last -> return n-1

2. Binary search:
   low = 1, high = n-2

3. mid calculate karo:
   mid = (low + high) / 2

4. Agar mid peak hai -> return mid

5. Agar left se bada hai (increasing slope) -> right jao
   low = mid + 1

6. Else -> left jao
   high = mid - 1

Time Complexity: O(log n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

One line intuition:
Jis side slope upar ja raha hai, peak usi side milega.

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int findPeakElement(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;

        if(n == 1) return 0;
        if(nums[0] > nums[1]){
            return 0;
        }
        if(nums[n-1] > nums[n-2]){
            return n-1;
        }
        int low = 1;
        int high = n-2;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;

            if(nums[mid] > nums[mid-1] && nums[mid] > nums[mid+1]){
                return mid;
            }

            //peak element is in right half
            else if(nums[mid-1] < nums[mid]){
                low = mid+1;
            }
            else{
                high = mid-1;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
